               <head>Works by Ni'mat Khan 'Ali</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of a work by Niʿmat Khān ʿĀlī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100074 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh89005046 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh89003718" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3782-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled compendious collection of prose (e.g., prefaces, letters, history) and poetry indicating this volume is a <title>kullīyāt</title> of the Iranian-born Timurid or Mughal court poet and courtier, Niʿmat Khān, also known as Dānishmand Khān, with the poetic pseudonym ʿĀlī
                        </p>
                        <p>Coloured and gilt rulings throughout; illuminated head pieces at the beginning of most sections probably added later; transcribed in shikastah and shafīʿah</p>
                        <p>Poor condition, with detaching text panels due to degrading pigments on thin paper </p>
                        <p>Some careful philological annotations added in margins, with reference to the <title>Farhang-i Jahāngīrī</title>
                        </p>
                        <p>Note on verso of first flyleaf and last (f. 271v): Fullekghar 1858</p>
                        <p>Multiple dated colophons at end of each major section (ff. 16v, 44v, 119v, 131r, 271v) indicating either a non-sequential order of production or that individual parts have been bound in an order different to order of completion: 1) completed 13 Rajab 1148/29 November 1735 in the ṣūbah of dār al-khilāfah Shāhjahān'ābād; 2) completed 16 Rajab 1148/2 December 1735 in the ṣūbah of Shāhjahān'ābād; 3) completed 4 Rajab 1148/20 November 1735 in the city of Dihlī; 4) completed 10 Shavvāl 1148/23 February 1736 in the ṣūbah of Shāhjahān'ābād; 5) completed 16 Ramaz̤ān 1148/30 January 1736 in the ṣūbah of Dihlī</p>
                        <p>IOL stamp: 13 May 1909</p>
                     </note>
